      <method name="dup_build_system"
              c:identifier="foundry_context_dup_build_system">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="libfoundry/foundry-context.c"
             line="2059">Gets the name of the build system to use.

First the settings are checked. If set, that is preferred. After that,
the configuration is checked to see if it specifies a build system.

Otherwise, %NULL is returned.

Build addins can also affect which build system is used and you may
check what the build pipeline thinks should be the build system (which
checks this value) by using [property@Foundry.BuildPipeline:build-system].</doc>
        <source-position filename="libfoundry/foundry-context.h" line="93"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="full" nullable="1">
          <doc xml:space="preserve"
               filename="libfoundry/foundry-context.c"
               line="2074">a build-system name or %NULL</doc>
          <type name="utf8" c:type="char*"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
