      <method name="merge_unix_fd_map"
              c:identifier="foundry_process_launcher_merge_unix_fd_map"
              throws="1">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="libfoundry/platform/foundry-process-launcher.c"
             line="1440">Merges the #FoundryUnixFDMap into the current layer.

If there are collisions in destination FDs, then that may cause an
error and %FALSE is returned.

@unix_fd_map will have the FDs stolen using foundry_unix_fd_map_steal_from()
which means that if successful, @unix_fd_map will not have any open
file-descriptors after calling this function.</doc>
        <source-position filename="libfoundry/platform/foundry-process-launcher.h"
                         line="122"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="none">
          <doc xml:space="preserve"
               filename="libfoundry/platform/foundry-process-launcher.c"
               line="1455">%TRUE if successful; otherwise %FALSE and @error is set.</doc>
