      <doc xml:space="preserve"
           filename="libfoundry/build/foundry-pty-diagnostics.c"
           line="37">Custom PTY intermediate that can extract diagnostics.</doc>
      <source-position filename="libfoundry/build/foundry-pty-diagnostics.h"
                       line="30"/>
      <implements name="Gio.ListModel"/>
      <implements name="Json.Serializable"/>
      <constructor name="new" c:identifier="foundry_pty_diagnostics_new">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="libfoundry/build/foundry-pty-diagnostics.c"
             line="574">@pty_fd should be a valid file-descriptor for the consumer side of the
PTY device. This is sometimes, historically, called the "master" side of
a PTY device.

@pty_fd will be `dup()`d.

You can use [method@Foundry.PtyDiagnostics.get_fd] to get a new synthetic
PTY consumer for which you can create a producer for and attach to
child processes.

The resulting [class@Foundry.PtyDiagnostics] is also a
[iface@Gio.ListModel] of [class@Foundry.Diagnostic] so you may use the
list model API to access diagnostics as they are discovered.</doc>
        <source-position filename="libfoundry/build/foundry-pty-diagnostics.h"
                         line="35"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="full">
          <type name="PtyDiagnostics" c:type="FoundryPtyDiagnostics*"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
          <parameter name="context" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="libfoundry/build/foundry-pty-diagnostics.c"
                 line="576">a [class@Foundry.Context]</doc>
            <type name="Context" c:type="FoundryContext*"/>
          </parameter>
          <parameter name="pty_fd" transfer-ownership="none">
            <doc xml:space="preserve"
                 filename="libfoundry/build/foundry-pty-diagnostics.c"
                 line="577">a file-descriptor for PTY consumer</doc>
            <type name="gint" c:type="int"/>
          </parameter>
        </parameters>
      </constructor>
      <function name="register"
                c:identifier="foundry_pty_diagnostics_register">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="libfoundry/build/foundry-pty-diagnostics.c"
             line="649">Registers @regex for use when extracting diagnostics from a PTY stream.

The regex should capture values into named groups that the
[class@Foundry.PtyDiagnostics] can turn into [class@Foundry.Diagnostic].

Named groups supported are:

 - message
 - filename
 - line
 - column
 - level</doc>
        <source-position filename="libfoundry/build/foundry-pty-diagnostics.h"
                         line="33"/>
        <return-value transfer-ownership="none">
          <type name="none" c:type="void"/>
        </return-value>
        <parameters>
          <parameter name="regex" transfer-ownership="full">
            <type name="GLib.Regex" c:type="GRegex*"/>
          </parameter>
        </parameters>
      </function>
