    <function name="file_read_link"
              c:identifier="foundry_file_read_link"
              version="1.1">
      <doc xml:space="preserve"
           filename="libfoundry/foundry-util.c"
           line="596">Asynchronously resolves @file if it is a symbolic link.

If @file is not a symbolic link (as determined by
[method@Gio.File.query_info] with
%G_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_STANDARD_IS_SYMLINK), the future resolves to @file
itself. If it is a symbolic link, the link target is read with
[func@GLib.file_read_link] and a new [iface@Gio.File] for the
resolved path is returned. On failure, the future rejects with an error.

The work is performed in a fiber on the thread pool scheduler.</doc>
      <source-position filename="libfoundry/foundry-util.h" line="59"/>
      <return-value transfer-ownership="full">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="libfoundry/foundry-util.c"
             line="611">a [class@Dex.Future] that resolves to a
  [iface@Gio.File], or rejects with [struct@GLib.Error]</doc>
        <type name="Dex.Future" c:type="DexFuture*"/>
      </return-value>
      <parameters>
        <parameter name="file" transfer-ownership="none">
          <doc xml:space="preserve"
               filename="libfoundry/foundry-util.c"
               line="598">a [iface@Gio.File]</doc>
          <type name="Gio.File" c:type="GFile*"/>
        </parameter>
      </parameters>
    </function>
    <function name="file_read_link_recurse"
              c:identifier="foundry_file_read_link_recurse"
              version="1.1">
      <doc xml:space="preserve"
           filename="libfoundry/foundry-util.c"
           line="557">Asynchronously resolves @file by repeatedly following symbolic links
until the result is not a symbolic link, or @max_depth steps have been
taken.

Uses a "seen" set to detect cycles: if the same [iface@Gio.File] is
encountered again while resolving, the future rejects with
%G_IO_ERROR_FAILED and message "Symbolic link loop detected".

The work is performed in a fiber on the thread pool scheduler.</doc>
      <source-position filename="libfoundry/foundry-util.h" line="61"/>
      <return-value transfer-ownership="full">
        <doc xml:space="preserve"
             filename="libfoundry/foundry-util.c"
             line="572">a [class@Dex.Future] that resolves to a
  [iface@Gio.File], or rejects with [struct@GLib.Error]</doc>
        <type name="Dex.Future" c:type="DexFuture*"/>
      </return-value>
      <parameters>
        <parameter name="file" transfer-ownership="none">
          <doc xml:space="preserve"
               filename="libfoundry/foundry-util.c"
               line="559">a [iface@Gio.File]</doc>
          <type name="Gio.File" c:type="GFile*"/>
        </parameter>
        <parameter name="max_depth" transfer-ownership="none">
          <doc xml:space="preserve"
               filename="libfoundry/foundry-util.c"
               line="560">maximum number of symbolic links to resolve (must be &gt; 0)</doc>
          <type name="guint" c:type="guint"/>
        </parameter>
      </parameters>
    </function>
